---
title: Calendar OAuth Flow With Token Protection
---
sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant TG as Telegram
    participant GW as bot-gateway
    participant CAL as calendar-service
    participant PG as PostgreSQL

    User->>TG: /calendar
    TG->>GW: update
    GW->>CAL: signed GET /connections?telegramUserId=X&scope=user
    Note over GW,CAL: HMAC + replay protection + signed user id
    CAL->>PG: read CalendarConnection
    CAL-->>GW: no connections

    GW->>CAL: signed POST /auth-url
    CAL->>CAL: create signed OAuth state
    CAL-->>GW: Google OAuth URL
    GW->>TG: show Connect Google Calendar button

    User->>TG: opens OAuth URL
    User->>CAL: Google redirects with code and state through gateway callback
    GW->>CAL: signed POST /oauth-callback
    CAL->>CAL: verify OAuth state signature
    CAL->>CAL: exchange code for tokens
    CAL->>CAL: encrypt refresh token
    CAL->>PG: save CalendarConnection
    CAL->>PG: write audit calendar.connected
    CAL-->>GW: connected
    GW->>TG: show connected status

    User->>TG: disconnect calendar
    TG->>GW: callback
    GW->>CAL: signed DELETE /connections
    CAL->>PG: remove connection
    CAL->>PG: write audit calendar.disconnected
    CAL-->>GW: ok
    GW->>TG: show disconnected status
